File: Cricket balls.  Paul ELLIS/AFP JOHANNESBURG - Proteas women batter Lizelle Lee and Proteas opener Janneman Malan are the only South Africans to be nominated for ICC Awards. READ: SA to co-host 2027 50-over Cricket World Cup Malan has been nominated for the ODI Cricketer of the Year after an impressive showing with the bat for the national team. He is the second-highest ODI run-scorer of the year with 509 runs in eight ODIs. Lee received two nominations, the ICC Women's Cricketer of the Year and the ICC Women's ODI Cricketer of the Year award. The 29-year-old led the Proteas’ charge in a series win against Pakistan, India, and West Indies. She scored 632 runs in 12 matches. Voting takes place via the ICC Website, starting on 5 January.